### Admin Profile Photo Management - Base64 Storage
### Replace {adminId} with actual admin ID from your database

### 1. Upload Profile Photo
POST http://localhost:8080/api/admins/{adminId}/profile-photo
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="photo"; filename="profile.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./path/to/your/image.jpg
--boundary--

### 2. Get Profile Photo Data (Base64)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/admins/{adminId}/profile-photo

### 3. Delete Profile Photo
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/admins/{adminId}/profile-photo

### 4. Get Admin Profile (to see profilePhoto field)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/admins/{adminId}

### 5. Update Admin Profile (other fields)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/admins/{adminId}/profile
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Updated Admin Name",
  "email": "updated@example.com",
  "phone": "+1234567890"
}

### 6. Get All Admins (to see which have photos)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/admins